<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="443" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1424,2037]" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1459,1482]" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head twice as long as width across eyes, prolonged in front of eyes over bases of antennae; compound eyes with few and weakly defined facets; cheeks slightly constricted behind eyes, vertex lacking sculpture except weakly reticulate along posterior margin; postocular setae long and finely pointed, maxillary stylets retracted to postocular setae, close together medially, mandible long and robust (
<figureCitation box="[704,768,1563,1586]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Antennae 8-segmented (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1150,1563,1586]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
); segment I the longest; II dorsally with 2 pairs of setae and campaniform sensillum in basal half, ventrally with long apical spur (
<figureCitation box="[1315,1384,1598,1621]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); III asymmetric with outer margin swollen and base slender, with 
<docIssue box="[820,833,1632,1655]" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">3</docIssue>
short stout sense cones, segment IV with 4; V–VI each with 2; IV–VIII bulbous with pedicels narrow. Pronotum with 5 pairs of slender pointed major setae but anteromarginal setae variable in length; notopleural sutures incomplete (
<figureCitation box="[752,817,1702,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); basantra absent but 2 or 3 setae present; ferna narrowing medially and almost meeting (
<figureCitation box="[473,538,1736,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); mesopraesternum and mesoeusternal margin eroded; pair of minute setae medially associated with eroded spinasternum. Mesonotum weakly reticulate on anterior margin; metanotum lacking sculpture with 2 long acute setae medially (
<figureCitation box="[522,590,1806,1829]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Fore tarsal tooth large and robust, ventro-lateral hamus prominent; mid and hind tibiae without stout setae. Pelta broadly triangular but partly eroded, with weak sculpture (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1242,1840,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[246,1342,776,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[246,1347,776,1957]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Kremnothrips epakrus sp. n. (1) head; (2) pronotum, meso- and metanota; (3) prosternites; (4) antenna; (5) antennal segment II ventral view; (6) pelta and tergite II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803211/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="443">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Tergite II lateral margins not eroded; III–VII with 2 long setae laterally, and anterior pair of wing-retaining setae small but posterior pair long and straight; tergite IX setae slightly longer than tube. Tube shorter than head with straight margins; anal setae shorter than tube. Sternites without reticulate areas.
</paragraph>
